cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the challenges of collecting and analyzing large-scale social media data in the context of political communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). The paper also discusses the use of natural language processing techniques for analyzing social media data, which makes cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible category. Finally, the paper addresses issues of data reliability and objectivity, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
